.TH CWE-77 7 "2025-12-11" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-77 \- Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in a Command (Command Injection)
.SH RANK
2025 CWE Top 25 rank: \fB#23\fR (2024 rank: 13).
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: Injection.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Untrusted input is incorporated into a command (to a shell, interpreter or other command processor) without neutralising elements that change which commands run. OS command injection (CWE\-78) is the best\-known child.
.SH MITIGATION
Avoid building commands from untrusted strings; use APIs that take an argument array, prefer native library calls over shelling out, and allow\-list acceptable values. Run with least privilege.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-15): \fB29\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
